# To get Genres form given String and convert them to LIST
def getGenres(a):
    count=a.count("name")
    genresList=[]
    while(count>0):
        start=a.find("name")
        end = a.find("}")
        genre = a[start+8:end-1]
        genresList.append(genre)
        count-=1
        a=a[end+1:]
    return genresList

# To get the URL of the Movie
def getUrl(title,year):
        listYears=[]
        listYears.append(year)
        listYears.append(year+1)
        listYears.append(year-1)
        
        a=""
        aa=""
        url= "https://www.imdb.com/find?q="+title+"&ref_=nv_sr_sm"
        url2=""
        page = get(url)
        soup = BeautifulSoup(page.content, 'lxml')
        content = soup.find(id="main")
        subContent = content.find_all("div", class_="findSection")

        for i in subContent:
            if("Titles" in i.find_all(class_="findSectionHeader")[0]):
                      a=i.find_all("td",class_="result_text")

        for it in a:
            if((str(year+1) in str(it)) or (str(year) in str(it))  or (str(year-1) in str(it)) ):
                #print((str(year+1) in str(it)) or (str(year) in str(it)) or (str(year-1) in str(it)))
                #print(it)
                #print(year)
                aa=it.find_all("a")[0]['href']
                url2="http://imdb.com"+aa
                break
        return url2

# To get the Storyline of the Movie
def getOverview(url):
    storyLine=""
    global iterV
    try:
        page = get(url)
        soup = BeautifulSoup(page.content, 'lxml')
        content = soup.find(id="main_bottom")
        subContent = content.find("div", class_="article",id="titleStoryLine")
        story = subContent.find("p")   
        storyLine = story.find("span").text.replace("span","").strip()
    except:
        iterV+=1
        print("Dude, your code sucked "+str(iterV)+" times :(" )
        return "NaN"
    
    return storyLine

# We define a helper function for visualization purposes
def to_membership_vector(partition):
    return {
        member :  partition_id
        for partition_id, members in enumerate(partition)
        for member in members
    }

# Function to print the word cloud of frequent words for a given Genre
def getWords(genreName):
    # To get words in genre
    words = ""
    for i in range(dfv['genres'].shape[0]):
        if genreName in str(dfv['genres'][i]):
            words+= dfv['words'][i] + " "
            
    # WordCloud
    cloud = WordCloud(background_color = "YelloW", max_words = 99, stopwords = set(STOPWORDS))
    cloud.generate(words)
    plt.figure(figsize=(9,18))
    plt.imshow(cloud)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

# To clean words with ' character.
def decontracted(phrase):
    # specific
    phrase = re.sub(r"won't", "will not", phrase)
    phrase = re.sub(r"can\'t", "can not", phrase)
    # general
    phrase = re.sub(r"n\'t", " not", phrase)
    phrase = re.sub(r"\'re", " are", phrase)
    phrase = re.sub(r"\'s", " is", phrase)
    phrase = re.sub(r"\'d", " would", phrase)
    phrase = re.sub(r"\'ll", " will", phrase)
    phrase = re.sub(r"\'t", " not", phrase)
    phrase = re.sub(r"\'ve", " have", phrase)
    phrase = re.sub(r"\'m", " am", phrase)
    # To remove repetetive words like aa bbb ccc
    phrase = re.sub(r"(.)\1{2,}","", phrase)
    return phrase

from tqdm import tqdm
preprocessed_overviews = []

for sentance in tqdm(df_genresWords['words'].values):
    sentance = re.sub(r"http\S+", "", sentance)
    sentance = BeautifulSoup(sentance, 'lxml').get_text()
    sentance = decontracted(sentance)
    sentance = re.sub("\S*\d\S*", "", sentance).strip()
    sentance = re.sub('[^A-Za-z]+', ' ', sentance)
    # https://gist.github.com/sebleier/554280
    sentance = ' '.join(e.lower() for e in sentance.split() if e.lower() not in stopwords)
    preprocessed_overviews.append(sentance.strip())
